Slicetrim is a Photoshop script to automatically trim away surrounding transparent space of slice.

Install:
1. Copy the script to <Photoshop_dir>\Presets\Scripts\.
2. Restart Photoshop.
3. Press Ctrl + Shift + Alt + K, then assign a shortcut to this script(e.g., Ctrl + F1 to call File => Scripts => slicetrim).

Usage:
1. Hide all other layers that aren't part of the slice.
2. Call the script from menu(File => Scripts => slicetrim) or press Ctrl + F1, then the slice is automatically created for you.
